      * 
      * -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
      * 
      * with_user_audit => true/false
      * - This flag tells the model to add these three fields:
      * 1. author - the user that creates a row
      * 2. modifier - the user that last updated a row
      * 3. remover - the user that deleted a row (If soft deletes are set)
      * 
      * - The above fields are OneToOne relation fields pointing to the User model.
      * - The specific names of the table columns associated with these fields are set with
      * the configurations:
      * 
      * author_column = 'author_id' //default, set yours if different
      * modifier_column = 'modifier_id' //default, set yours if different
      * remover_column = 'remover_id' //default, set yours if different
      * 
      * -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
