      * 2. modified_at - the timestamp of when a row was last updated. This is a DateTime field
      * 3. removed_at - the timestamp of when the row was deleted. This is a DateTime field (If soft deletes are set)
      * 
      * - the specific names of the table columns associated with these fields are similar to the field names,
      * but can be changed with the configurations below:
      * 
      * created_at_column = 'created_at' //default, set yours if different
      * modified_at_column = 'modified_at' //default, set yours if different
